    },
    "body": "Fixes #34262\n\nStop HTTP RPC requests from entering command execution after shutdown starts. This keeps queued getblocktemplate requests from reaching mining teardown while preserving the existing CHECK_NONFATAL.\n\nAdds a regression case that fills RPC workers with getblocktemplate longpolls, queues another getblocktemplate request, sends SIGTERM, and verifies clean shutdown and the expected shutdown RPC error.\n\nChecks:\n- cmake --build build --target bitcoind bitcoin-cli test_bitcoin -j$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu)\n- build/test/functional/test_runner.py --jobs=1 mining_basic.py feature_shutdown.py feature_notifications.py\n- build/test/functional/test_runner.py --jobs=1 mining_getblocktemplate_longpoll.py\n- build/bin/test_bitcoin -t rpc_tests\n- git diff --check",
    "labels": [
      {
        "id": 98279177,
        "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw5ODI3OTE3Nw==",
